text: Patagoniodes is a snout moth genus in the subfamily Phycitinae described by Rolf-Ulrich Roesler in 1969. It currently contains seven species , of which Patagoniodes popescugorji is the type species ==Species== *Patagoniodes farinaria (Turner, 1904) *Patagoniodes hoenei Roesler, 1969 *Patagoniodes kurtharzi Roesler, 1983 *Patagoniodes likiangella Roesler, 1969 *Patagoniodes nipponella Ragonot, 1901 *Patagoniodes popescugorji Roesler, 1969 *Patagoniodes semari Roesler & Kuppers, 1981 ==References== Category:Phycitinae ==External links==
title: Patagoniodes
